Day 1 — Introduction to Java + First Program
1. What is Java

Java is a high-level programming language used to build:

Android apps
Web applications
Enterprise software

Big companies like Amazon and Netflix use Java in backend systems.

Two important properties:

• Platform independent – write once, run anywhere
• Object-oriented language

Example:
You write code on Windows → it runs on Linux or Mac.

2. Java Program Structure

Every Java program follows this structure.

Example 1

public class Hello {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello World");
    }
}

Example 2

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Welcome Vishnu");
    }
}

Explanation:

public class Hello
→ Class name.

main()
→ Starting point of the program.

System.out.println()
→ Prints output.

3. Output Statement

System.out.println() prints text on screen.

Example 1

System.out.println("Hello");

Output

Hello

Example 2

System.out.println("I am learning Java");

Output

I am learning Java
4. Rules of Java

Important rules beginners miss:

File name must match class name
Java is case sensitive

Wrong

system.out.println("Hello");

Correct

System.out.println("Hello");
